      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: show official owner badges across public surfaces",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Compute `owner.official` from the existing row-backed policy: the exact owner publisher must have an `officialPublishers` row.\n- Carry `owner.official` through public skill detail, digest-backed skill lists/search results, package detail, and the v1 package/skill response schemas.\n- Render compact Official badges from either `skill.badges.official` or `owner.official`, including browse cards/rows and plugin owner metadata.\n\n## Intentional Surfaces\nThe coverage is intentional. Several public pages are built from different backend shapes: live skill rows, search digests, package detail, and HTTP API fallback data. This PR makes those shapes agree on the same `owner.official` field.\n\n| Surface | What changed | Why this is in scope |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Skill detail: `/$owner/$slug` via `skills.getBySlug` | Skill detail owners now include row-backed `owner.official`. | A skill owned by an official publisher should show the same owner badge as publisher pages. |\n| Main browse and search: `/skills`, `/skills?sort=...`, filters, and direct search results | Digest-backed entries now add `owner.official` from `officialPublishers`. | Sorting/filtering/searching should not change whether an official owner badge appears. |\n| Browse card and row UI | `SkillListItem` and the grid `SkillsResults` cards pass owner metadata into badge calculation. | The backend can now send `owner.official`; the visible cards need to use it. |\n| Related, trending, highlighted, and audit skill entries | Shared digest entry builders add the same owner official metadata. | These use the same public entry shape as browse/search and should not drift. |\n| Package detail API: `/api/v1/packages/:name` | Package and skill-package detail owner JSON can include `owner.official`. | Plugin pages load through this API, so owner badges need the same field there. |\n| Plugin detail UI: `/plugins/$name` | Owner metadata renders the compact Official badge when `owner.official` is true. | The title-level Official tag already existed; this adds the missing owner-level badge. |\n| Public schemas and docs | v1 schema packages accept optional `owner.official`; HTTP docs mention the field. | API clients need the optional field in the typed contract. |\n\n## Before / After Evidence\nScreenshots were captured locally from before/after runs and are hosted on `pr-evidence/2407-official-badges` so this PR can show the images without adding screenshot files to this diff.\n\n| Area | Before | After |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Main browse: `/skills?sort=downloads` | `Codex Owner Move Debug` had 0 Official badges.<br><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openclaw/clawhub/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/docs/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/before-main-skills-downloads.png\" alt=\"Before main browse downloads\" width=\"420\"> | `Codex Owner Move Debug` has the compact Official badge from `owner.official`.<br><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openclaw/clawhub/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/docs/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/after-pr-skills-downloads.png\" alt=\"After main browse downloads\" width=\"420\"> |\n| Official publisher skill detail: `/steipete/codex-owner-move-debug-1778257045` | 0 compact Official badges, 0 title Official tags.<br><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openclaw/clawhub/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/docs/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/before-main-steipete-skill-detail.png\" alt=\"Before steipete skill detail\" width=\"420\"> | Owner badge appears and the title Official tag appears through `owner.official`.<br><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openclaw/clawhub/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/docs/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/after-pr-steipete-skill-detail.png\" alt=\"After steipete skill detail\" width=\"420\"> |\n| OpenClaw plugin detail: `/plugins/@openclaw/whatsapp` | Title Official tag existed, but owner metadata missed the compact badge.<br><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openclaw/clawhub/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/docs/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/before-main-openclaw-plugin-detail.png\" alt=\"Before OpenClaw plugin detail\" width=\"420\"> | Title Official tag remains and owner metadata shows the compact Official badge.<br><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openclaw/clawhub/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/docs/pr-evidence/2407-official-badges/after-pr-openclaw-plugin-detail.png\" alt=\"After OpenClaw plugin detail\" width=\"420\"> |\n\n## Validation\n- `bun run format:check` passed.\n- `bun run lint` passed.\n- `bun run test convex/lib/officialPublishers.test.ts convex/skills.public.test.ts convex/packages.public.test.ts convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts convex/skills.publicListCursor.test.ts convex/skills.publicModeration.test.ts convex/skills.staffAuditLogs.test.ts convex/skills.versions.public.test.ts convex/search.test.ts packages/schema/src/schemas.test.ts src/lib/badges.test.ts src/components/SkillListItem.test.tsx src/routes/skills/-SkillsResults.test.tsx src/__tests__/package-detail-route.test.tsx` passed: 14 files, 611 tests.\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/schema/tsconfig.json --noEmit` passed.\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub/tsconfig.json --noEmit` passed.\n",
        "branch": "jesse/official-badge-surfaces",
